By phylogenetic analysis, ZIKV isolates cluster into two lineages, namely African and Asian (
 Haddow et al., 2012). Epidemic ZIKV strains from French Polynesia and the Americas cluster are included in the Asian lineage of ZIKV (
 Lanciotti et al., 2016). African strains have been shown to induce a more cytopathic effect 
 in vitro in comparison to Asian strains (
 Anfasa et al., 2017; 
 Bhatnagar et al., 2017; 
 Yuan et al., 2017; 
 Sheridan et al., 2018). It is speculated that Asian strains induce less cytopathic effect and maintain cell viability to allow a longer period of viral persistence and replication (
 Sheridan et al., 2018).
